1
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:25,000
Basûfan, gundê êzidiya yê dîrokî ye, ku dikeve aliyê başûrê
rojavayê navçeya Şêrawayê ya girêdayî bajar û gundewarên
Sûriyê de hatiye avakirin.
 
Basufan is a historic Yazidi village, built in the southwest
of the Sherawa district, which is connected to the city and
rural areas of Syria.

2
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Dîroka vî gundî digihêje 700 ta 800 sal berî zayînê.
 
The history of this village dates back 700 to 800 years
before Christ.

3
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:39,000
Basûfan wekî erdîgariyekê bi çar kîlometreyan ji çiyayê
Sem'anê bi dûr dikeve û li aliyê bakurê rojavayê Kelê ye.
 
Basufan, geographically, is located four kilometers away
from Mount Simeon and lies to the northwest of the Castle.

4
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:42,000
Di heman demê de li aliyê başûrê kantona Efrînê ye.
 
At the same time, it is located in the south of the Afrin
canton.

5
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:49,000
Di derbarê navlêkirina gund û li gorî çavkaniyên herêmî wiha
hatiye gotin:
 
Regarding the naming of the village, according to local
sources, it is said:

6
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Baso, ji ber ku tîpa 'Z' û 'S' di kurdî de dadigerin ser
hev, gengaz e ku Bazo be.
 
Baso, because the letters 'Z' and 'S' interchange in
Kurdish, it is possible that it is Bazo.

7
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Bi vî awayî dibe Bazo Fan.
 
In this way, it becomes Bazo Fan.

8
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:06,000
Tê zanîn ku li bakurê Kurdistanê li ser sînorê Amedê nêzîkî
wan e li herêma Qerejdaxê gundek bi vî navî tê naskirin.
 
It is known that in northern Kurdistan, on the border of
Amed, close to them in the Karacadağ region, a village is
known by this name.

9
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:26,000
Basûfan, ji ber bilindbûn û dûzbûna wê bi rûyê deryayê re,
di hêla ku bayekî har û sar peyda dibe, Bazo dibe ku
têkildarî 'Ba zû hatinê' be.
 
Basufan, due to its high and flat elevation relative to sea
level, which creates a fierce and cold wind, Bazo might be
related to 'Ba zû hatinê' (fast wind coming).

10
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:45,000
Temaşevanên hêja, vê carê em li gundê Basûfanê ne. Ev gundê
Basûfanê jî girêdayî navçeya Şêrawayê ye.
 
Dear viewers, this time we are in the village of Basufan.
This village of Basufan is connected to the Sherawa
district.

11
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Ev gund bi taybetî hemû kurdên me yên êzidî ne.
 
This village in particular is entirely populated by our
Yazidi Kurds.

12
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:54,000
Em berî cejnê jî hatin, me got em urf edetê gelê me yê êzidî
nas bikin sibe da cejn e.
 
We came before the holiday, we said let's get to know the
customs and traditions of our Yazidi people, tomorrow is a
holiday.

13
00:01:54,000 --> 00:02:12,000
Ev gund 360 mal in, de ka vê heftê em derbasî vî gundî
bibin.
 
This village has 360 houses, let's enter this village this
week.

14
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:25,000
Li gorî hin çavkaniyan jî, ev nav ji sofiyekî hatiye
wergirtin, ku berê hemû kes di herêma vî gundî û beriya
mirîd, şêx û pîrên êzîdî da hatine dermankirin.
 
According to some sources, this name was derived from a
Sufi, by whom everyone in the area of this village was
treated before the arrival of the Yazidi murids, sheikhs,
and pirs.

15
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:32,000
Piştî damezirandina mîrnişîna Mîtan û Horiyan, mîrnişîna
Xaltiyan li van deveran hatiye avakirin.
 
After the establishment of the Mitanni and Hurrian
principalities, the Xaltiyan principality was established in
these areas.

16
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Û ta radeyekê fireh bûye.
 
And to a certain extent it expanded.

17
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Basûfan, gundê êzidî mûra xwe di vê mîrnişînê de hiştiye.
 
Basufan, the Yazidi village, left its mark in this
principality.

18
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Tê zanîn ku di sala 1930'yî de, 85 gundên êzidî li van
deveran hebûn û nîştecihên wan hemû Xaltî bûn.
 
It is known that in the 1930s, there were 85 Yazidi villages
in these areas, and their inhabitants were all Xalti.

19
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:58,000
Hin gundên wekî Xalta, Qermîtliq, Maratê û her wekî din cihê
xwe di nav vê mîrnişînê de girtibûn.
 
Some villages like Xalta, Qermitliq, Marate, and others had
taken their place in this principality.

20
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:07,000
Lê bi hatina Osmaniyan û belavkirina ola Îslamê re gundên ku
di destpêkê de yekemîn tûşî pişaftin û qirkirinê bûn.
 
But with the arrival of the Ottomans and the spread of
Islam, these villages were the first to face assimilation
and genocide.

21
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:11,000
Bi yên di çiyayên da, ta radeyekê li ber xwe dan.
 
Those in the mountains resisted to a certain extent.

22
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Basûfan, yek ji wan gundê berxwedêr e.
 
Basufan is one of those resisting villages.

23
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:17,000
Ku xwe di çiyayên da parast.
 
That protected itself in the mountains.

24
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:36,000
Lê Erebîzmê ev rastî di rûpelên xwe de neaniye ziman.
 
But Arabism did not mention this truth in its pages.

25
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:39,000
Temaşevanên hêja, em derbasî gundê Basûfanê bûn.
 
Dear viewers, we have entered the village of Basufan.

26
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:45,000
Em hatin malek kevnar rûniştin, malek pir kevn e, xaniyekî
kevn e, ev dibêjinê xaniyê qentirmeyan e.
 
We came and sat down in an ancient house, a very old house,
an old building, they call this a vaulted house.

27
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:48,000
Ev gundî jî, hemî hatine li derdora me.
 
And these villagers have all gathered around us.

28
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:51,000
Beriya cejnê bi rojekê em hatin vî gundî.
 
We came to this village one day before the holiday.

29
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:58,000
Lê li kêleka min e wezîrê karê derve, birêz Silêman Cefer û
endamê komela êzidiyan e.
 
Next to me is the foreign affairs minister, Mr. Silêman
Cefer, who is also a member of the Yazidi association.

30
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Merheba ji we re.
 
Hello to you.

31
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,000
Sipas, bi xêr hatin.
 
Thank you, welcome.

32
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:08,000
Saq be. Mamoste me got em du rojekê hatin cem we, me got em
li ser dîroka gundê we nas bikin û sibeda jî cejna we ye.
 
Stay healthy. Teacher, we came to you for a couple of days
to learn about the history of your village, and tomorrow is
your holiday.

33
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,000
Bi rûmet û xêr hatine.
 
Welcome with honor and goodness.

34
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:12,000
Wekî bernameya ax û welat.
 
As the 'Ax û Welat' program.

35
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:15,000
Ev bernameyeke heyî xwaş î şêrîn.
 
This is a very nice and sweet program.

36
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:21,000
Ev bernameyê gelêrî bi rastî hemû temaşevan ji dil hez
dikin, çi li derve çi li hundir.
 
Truly all viewers love this popular program from the heart,
whether inside or outside (everywhere).

37
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:27,000
Tabî ev jî derbasî gundê xwe bûn îro, wekî rojekî dîrokî ye
em dikarin bibêjin rojeke olî ye.
 
Of course, you have entered your own village today, it is
like a historical day, we can say it is a religious day.

38
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,000
Rojekî bi qedr û qîmet e.
 
It is a day of worth and value.

39
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:36,000
Em gelê xwe re, me got em ê hêvî bikin cejna xwe derbas
bikin.
 
We said to our people, we hope to celebrate our holiday.

40
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,000
Lê mixabin îsal...
 
But unfortunately this year...

41
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:43,000
Me biryar da ku îsal em wekî her sal şahî yan em çênakin li
derva naxwin.
 
We decided that this year, unlike every year, we won't have
celebrations or eat outside.

42
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:48,000
Ji ber ku em xemgîn in, miletê me di warekî pir xemgîn de
dijî.
 
Because we are sad, our people are living in a very sad
situation.

43
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:56,000
Ji ber ku karesata ku hatî serê kurdan û êzidiyan bi taybetî
li Şengalê, ne însanî bû, nayê qebûlkirin.
 
Because the disaster that befell the Kurds and specifically
the Yazidis in Sinjar was not humane, it is unacceptable.

44
00:04:56,000 --> 00:05:06,000
Û wazîra şerê li Kobanê ketiye meha çaran, ev jî miletê me
yanî hemû fkir û nêrîna xwe li ser vî şerî ye.
 
And the war in Kobane has entered its fourth month, so our
people's thoughts and views are all focused on this war.

45
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:10,000
Wan xort û keçên me yên ku li çeperan da şer dikin, ruhê xwe
feda dikin.
 
Our young men and women who are fighting in the trenches are
sacrificing their souls.

46
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:13,000
Fikrê me li cem wan e ne li cem şahiyan e.
 
Our thoughts are with them, not with celebrations.

47
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:19,000
Me bi tenê me got em îsal bila ev cejn wekî bi duayên, dua
derbas bibin.
 
We just said let this year's holiday pass only with prayers.

48
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Hetanî em bi hêvî ya sala tê Şengala xwe rizgarkin, û Kobanê
rizgar bikin, em hemû hevdura, vê cejnê em ê... pîroz bikin.
 
Until, we hope, by next year, we liberate our Sinjar and
Kobane, and together we will... celebrate this holiday.

49
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:37,000
Û bi hêviya hemû girtiyên zindanan de jî derkevin, em bi
hevdura vê cejnê kefxwaşî şahî bikin.
 
And with the hope that all the prisoners will be released
from the prisons, together we will celebrate this holiday
with joy.

50
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:41,000
Mamoste ev sê roj in rojiya digrin ev jî rojên dawiyê ye.
 
Teacher, it has been three days of fasting, and these are
the final days.

51
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:48,000
Tabî, rojiya me weke êzidî, olê gelê êzidî rojiyên me gelek
in, ne hindik in bêjim.
 
Of course, our fasting as Yazidis, in the religion of the
Yazidi people we have many fasts, not just a few, I must
say.

52
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:54,000
Lê her weke, çele, du çele hene her çeleyek 40 roj heye.
 
Like the 'çele' (forty days), there are two 'çeles', each is
40 days.

53
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:59,000
Lê hemû êzîdî nikarin van çelayan bigirin, çeleyê havînê ye
û çeleyê zivistanê heye.
 
But not all Yazidis can observe these fasts, there's a
summer 'çele' and a winter 'çele'.

54
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:01,000
Xeyrî wê jî pir roje hene.
 
Apart from that, there are many fasts.

55
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:07,000
Weke ev ên hîro ev 3 roj rojî ye, dibêjin rojiyê êzî.
 
Like today's fast, it is a 3-day fast, they call it the fast
of Ezi.

56
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:14,000
Lê berî wê du hefteyên din girtin, hefteya yekemîn rojiya
Şêşems, pê re rojiya Xwedan.
 
But before that, two other weeks were observed. The first
week is the fast of Şêşems, followed by the fast of Xwedan.

57
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:18,000
Pey rojiya Xwedan re em dinê, cejna, ev rojiya Êzî.
 
After the fast of Xwedan, we have the holiday, this fast of
Ezi.

58
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,000
Ev jî ji ku hatiye?
 
Where does this come from?

59
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:23,000
Yanî ev tabi dîrokî wan jî pir kevin e.
 
I mean, of course, their history is also very old.

60
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:28,000
Em ku em vegerin destpêkê waxta... dinê însan derkete...
 
If we go back to the beginning, when... people came into the
world...

61
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Yanî nizane, xêr û şer çiye.
 
I mean, they didn't know what good and evil were.

62
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:32,000
Nizanî ev çiye.
 
They didn't know what this was.

63
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:38,000
Bav û kalên xwe danîn, yanî ev dibêjin inqîlaba şitewî, ev
inqîlaba faslî.
 
Our ancestors established it, I mean they call it the winter
solstice, the seasonal solstice.

64
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,000
Nizanin.
 
They didn't know.

65
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:50,000
Dîtin hêdî hêdî roj reş dibe, digotin reş nîşana şer e. Û
ronahî jî nîşana xêrê ye.
 
They saw the day slowly getting darker, they said black is
the sign of evil. And light is the sign of good.

66
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:55,000
Bav û kalên wan dîtin her ku roj kurt dibe, dinê jî reş
dibe.
 
Their ancestors saw that whenever the day gets shorter, the
world also gets darker.

67
00:06:55,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Ve ji ber wê, gotin ka em li ber xwedê xwe bigerin, am ber
rojê bigerin. Gelo roj nere.
 
And because of this, they said let us turn to our God, let
us turn to the sun. Wondering if the sun won't go away.

68
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:04,000
Sê roj, rojî girtin.
 
They fasted for three days.

69
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:08,000
Ber xwedê xwe geriyan ku roj ev ber rojê geriyan belkî roj
nare.
 
They turned to their God, they turned to the sun, hoping the
sun won't go away.

70
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,000
Roj hîn daket.
 
The sun set even more.

71
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:11,000
Pê re, 3 roj din jî girtin.
 
Then, they fasted for another 3 days.

72
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:16,000
Ji bo xudanê xwe her kes, em dîn wek êzdî her yeko xudanê
xwe hene.
 
For their master, everyone, we as Yazidis, everyone has
their own master.

73
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:21,000
Yanî xudan xudanê ocaxê wan hene, sê roj dîsa rojî girtin
dîsa roj hîn kêm bû.
 
I mean, masters, they have masters of their hearth, they
fasted for three days again, the sun decreased even more.

74
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:23,000
Roj hefteya din, 3'yê dawiyê.
 
The sun, the next week, the 3 days of the end.

75
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:27,000
Dema roji girtin, bav û kalên wan dîtin roj sekinî.
 
When they fasted, their ancestors saw the sun stop.

76
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:33,000
Got çi? Go me rojî girt... bi wê rojiya girtî em gihan
xwedê, yanî xwedê rojida me qebûl kir.
 
They said what? They said we fasted... with that fast we
reached God, I mean God accepted our fast.

77
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,000
Tu wateyeke xeyrî vê tuneye.
 
There is no other meaning besides this.

78
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:40,000
Yanî çawa me rojî girt, me kanîbû roj bê rawestandin ji
tunebûnê, ji windabûnê.
 
I mean, how we fasted, we were able to stop the sun from
ceasing, from disappearing.

79
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:42,000
Mamoste, çend cejnê we hene?
 
Teacher, how many holidays do you have?

80
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:45,000
Wek min gotiye cejnên me e salekê şeş in.
 
As I said, we have six holidays a year.

81
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:50,000
Lê em.. em e Çarşemba Nisanê ye, e 3 cejnan ne.
 
But we... we have the Wednesday of April, it is 3 holidays.

82
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:53,000
E.. Xidir Îlyas e, e... Qurbanê ye.
 
There's... Khidir Ilyas, there's... the Sacrifice holiday.

83
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:59,000
Tabî e.. Qurbanê jî naha pirek jî nizanin, dibêjin ya, me
navê Îbrahîm Xelîl girtin.
 
Of course, many do not know about the Sacrifice holiday now,
they say 'yeah, we took the name of Ibrahim Khalil'.

84
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:06,000
Bi me, cejna Qurbanê em e, em Kurd in êzîdî ji... ji
pêxember Îbrahîm Xelîl de maye, Îbrahîm Xelîl jî bi xwe Kurd
bû, Kurdê Êzîdî bû jî bê guman.
 
To us, the Sacrifice holiday is ours, we are Yazidi Kurds,
it originates from... from Prophet Ibrahim Khalil. Ibrahim
Khalil himself was Kurdish, he was a Yazidi Kurd too,
undoubtedly.

85
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:14,000
Mamoste... Wekî gundê we dîroka gundê we ev çend sale
avabûye ev çend mal in bi taybetî çî di gund de dijîn?
 
Teacher... Like your village, the history of your village,
how many years ago was it built, how many houses are there,
and specifically what do they live on in the village?

86
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:18,000
Vê gundê me, dîroka xwe pir kevn e koka min bêjim.
 
This village of ours, its history is very old, its roots, I
should say.

87
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:23,000
Nav wek tiştî hatî gundê me bi etîbar gundê me.
 
The name came as something to our village, as it is
considered our village.

88
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:28,000
Di navbera me û bahrê, bahre sipî ti çiya tine ne.
 
Between us and the sea, the Mediterranean Sea, there are no
mountains.

89
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:32,000
Yekser hewayê e.. bahrê sipî yekser tê gundê me.
 
Directly the air of the... Mediterranean Sea comes straight
to our village.

90
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,000
Hewayê xwe pir sar e û pir heye.
 
Its weather is very cold and very abundant.

91
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:40,000
Ji ber wê navê xwe kirin Bazo Van. Bazo Van tê mane wekî
bahoz. Wekî em erebî dibêjin 'asîfe'.
 
Because of this they named it Bazo Van. Bazo Van means like
a storm. Like we say 'asîfe' in Arabic.

92
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:44,000
Heta rind tê bîra min, di pirtûkek da min xwend.
 
I even remember well, I read it in a book.

93
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,000
Dibêjin...
 
They say...

94
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:49,000
Berî niha bi 40, 50 salî, îsanekî li Helebê nexweş dibiya.
 
40, 50 years ago, if a person got sick in Aleppo.

95
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:55,000
Digot, here Basûfanê, hewaya wê paqij e, dê te xweş bike.
Wekî stîcmam dikirin.
 
They used to say, 'Go to Basufan, its air is clean, it will
heal you.' Like they were doing recreation.

96
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,000
Ve ji ber wê ev nav jê re hatiye.
 
And because of this, this name was given to it.

97
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:58,000
Çend malbat, di vî gundî de ne?
 
How many families are in this village?

98
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:04,000
Bi xwa em, wekê Êzdî, em çend... malbat in... tebeqat hene.
 
Actually, we, as Yazidis, we are a few... families... there
are classes.

99
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:09,000
Tebeqên dînî 3 tebeqa êzdîyan ên esas hene, tebeqa şêx û pîr
û mrîd.
 
The 3 basic religious classes of the Yazidis, the class of
the Sheikhs, the Pirs, and the Murids.

100
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:12,000
Lê gundê Basûfanê hemî gundî hemî şêx in.
 
But the village of Basufan, all the villagers are entirely
Sheikhs.

101
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:18,000
Sê... sê fexdên şêxan in, Nasir Dîn... e Şêxmend... e
Şêxbekir in.
 
Three... three branches of Sheikhs, Nasir Din... uh
Shexmand... uh Shexbekir.

102
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:23,000
Em gundê xwe ji vî gundê Basûfanê, ji van her sê şaxan,
peyda bûne.
 
Our village from this village of Basufan, are descended from
these three branches.

103
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:28,000
Hejmara wan jî naha gihêştin nêzîkî dorek 360 malî.
 
Their number has now reached around 360 houses.

104
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,000
Di nav Basûfanê.
 
Inside Basufan.

105
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:34,000
Hêjmara nifûsa jî naha gehaştin dorî, dor doro.. e 3500 din
e.
 
The population number has now reached around, around.. uh
3500.

106
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,000
Gundekî pir fireh bûye.
 
It has become a very large village.

107
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:43,000
Yanî bi tebîriya min gund, sedî ez kanim bibêjim rûbekî vî
gundî li dervayî welêt li xerîbiyê ne.
 
I mean, in my estimation, I can say a quarter of this
village are abroad in foreign lands.

108
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:48,000
Mamoste niha li derdora vê şêrawayê tenê ev gundê we êzidî
ne yan gundên din jî hene?
 
Teacher, now in this surrounding area of Sherawa, is it only
your village that is Yazidi, or are there other villages?

109
00:09:48,000 --> 00:10:00,000
