00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:10,000
Vaye li dor mezelan, xizm û heval, bîranînên wan...
 
Here around the graves, relatives and friends, their
memories...

424
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:27,000
bi dilsoziyeke parve dikin, û stêran ji bo wan jî dibarînin.
 
they share with loyalty, and they also shed tears for them.

425
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:32,000
Temaşevanên hêja, îro em hatine vir, miletê vir, civat jî,
hatine ser goristanê jî.
 
Dear viewers, today we have come here, the people here, the
community too, have come to the cemetery as well.

426
00:41:32,000 --> 00:41:34,000
Naha em ê ji wan bipirsin bê ew çi dibêjin.
 
Now we will ask them what they are saying.

427
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:42,000
Em cejna Êzîdî, em tên nav tirba, cihê goristanê.
 
On the Yazidi holiday, we come into the tomb, the place of
the cemetery.

428
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:47,000
Û em destpêkê bi rengê wek fatihayekê em dixwînin, li ser
miriyê xwe.
 
And at first, we recite something like an opening prayer,
over our dead.

429
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:50,000
Emê naha ji we re bêjin.
 
We will recite it to you now.

430
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:52,000
Bi navê Yezdanê dilovan ê bexşevan.
 
In the name of God, the compassionate, the forgiving.

431
00:41:52,000 --> 00:42:00,000
Amîn Amîn Xwedêyo alîkariya dîn, bi hîmeta Şemsedîn,
Fexredîn, Nasirdîn, Babadîn, Şêx Şems quweta dîn.
 
Amen, Amen, O God, help the religion, by the effort of
Shamsuddin, Fakhruddin, Nasiruddin, Babadin, Sheikh Shams
the power of religion.

432
00:42:00,000 --> 00:42:04,000
Siltan Şêxadî tac e, ji ewilî heta dawîn, heq tu yî ya Rebil
Alemîn.
 
Sultan Sheikh Adi is the crown, from the beginning to the
end, you are the truth, O Lord of the Worlds.

433
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:06,000
Xêran bide, şeran wergerîne.
 
Bestow goodness, turn away evils.

434
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:10,000
Mehderkê dixwazim bi rehma Şêxadî, riza Melekşêxhesen,
kerema Şêxşems.
 
I ask for a refuge with the mercy of Sheikh Adi, the consent
of Melek Sheikh Hasan, the grace of Sheikh Shams.

435
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:13,000
Şehda dînê me her ewa her ewa her ewa.
 
The testimony of our religion is always this, always this,
always this.

436
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:16,000
Wî ne xwarin, ne vexwarin, ne xew e.
 
He has no eating, no drinking, no sleep.

437
00:42:16,000 --> 00:42:36,000
Şehda baweriya min bi navê Xwedê û Tawisî Melek dihewe.
 
The testimony of my belief is contained in the name of God
and Tawus Melek.

438
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:45,000
Şengal, helbesta azadiyê, di guhê her kurdekî Êzîdî de...
 
Shengal, the poem of freedom, in the ear of every Yazidi
Kurd...

439
00:42:45,000 --> 00:42:48,000
malikên berxwedanê diçikîne.
 
plants the stanzas of resistance.

440
00:42:48,000 --> 00:42:51,000
Çaranûsiyek e, bedena me yek e.
 
It is a destiny, our body is one.

441
00:42:51,000 --> 00:42:57,000
Mîras, basofan, xisleta kurdîtiyê û nijada resen ji bo
Şengalê vedibêje.
 
Heritage, Basofan, the trait of Kurdishness and the
authentic race speak for Shengal.

442
00:42:57,000 --> 00:42:59,000
Şûnwarên pêşiyên dê û baban...
 
The relics of the ancestors of mothers and fathers...

443
00:42:59,000 --> 00:43:03,000
hêviyan pey bi tavê re bilind dike.
 
elevate the hopes along with the sun.

444
00:43:03,000 --> 00:43:06,000
da ku stûnên stûxwarî û dîroka çalkirî...
 
so that the bowed pillars and the buried history...

445
00:43:06,000 --> 00:43:26,000
careke din bi destê nifşên pêşerojê... bên avakirin.
 
can be rebuilt once again by the hands of future
generations.

446
00:43:28,000 --> 00:43:34,000
Temaşevanên hêja me gundê şên û xweş, gundê Basofanê, me
xatirê xwe ji gund xwest.
 
Dear viewers, we have bid farewell to the beautiful and
lively village, the village of Basofan.

447
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:38,000
Me xatirê xwe ji wan jî xwest, me dîroka vî gundî naskir.
 
We bid farewell to them as well, we got to know the history
of this village.

448
00:43:38,000 --> 00:43:40,000
Me urf û adetên me Êzîdiyan naskir.
 
We got to know the customs and traditions of us Yazidis.

449
00:43:40,000 --> 00:43:42,000
Heta hefteyeke din, em ê dîsa bi hev re bin.
 
Until another week, we will be together again.

450
00:43:42,000 --> 00:43:47,000
Li benda me bin.
 
Wait for us.

